metadata.name: Setsubunso flower awakening from the thaw
metadata.description:
Setubunsou is a Japanese endemic flower that blooms west of Kanto area in Japan.
This setsubunsou woke up today in the lingering snow and in the early spring, looking around a little, setsubunsou himself says that spring has come,
While looking around, I feel like setsubunsou is confirming that it's okay to wake up.
A true spring awakening.
A little bewildered, but also thrilled with joy, he seemed to whistle involuntarily and say hello to his friends.
In Japan, there is something called "setsu" as a turning point for each season, and Setsubun is an important time that represents the first turning point.
